  <notes>
    <note date="2026-01-29">
      ## Fix Applied

      **Root Cause (from Task 001)**: IToolHandlerRegistry was conditionally registered.
      When ToolFramework:Enabled = false, AppOnlyAnalysisService couldn't be instantiated,
      which caused AppOnlyDocumentAnalysisJobHandler to be excluded from the handler list.

      **Changes Made to Program.cs**:

      1. **Startup Diagnostics** (after `var app = builder.Build()`):
         - Logs all registered IJobHandler types at startup
         - Warns if expected handlers are missing
         - Helps diagnose "NoHandler" errors quickly

      2. **Fallback IToolHandlerRegistry Registration** (in else block for ToolFramework):
         - Always registers IToolHandlerRegistry even when framework disabled
         - Ensures AppOnlyAnalysisService can be instantiated
         - Prevents silent DI failures

      **Build Result**: ✅ Success (0 errors, 1 unrelated warning)

      **Acceptance Criteria**:
      - ✅ Handler exists at Services/Jobs/Handlers/AppOnlyDocumentAnalysisJobHandler.cs
      - ✅ Handler registered at Program.cs:622 + fallback IToolHandlerRegistry ensures it works
      - ✅ JobType = "AppOnlyDocumentAnalysis" (verified in Task 001)
      - ✅ Build succeeds
    </note>
